that it will take my son's life.

375
00:30:59,942 --> 00:31:03,838
It has mutated
and become drug resistant.

376
00:31:03,918 --> 00:31:08,387
All the antibiotics that we could get
don't work on him anymore.

377
00:31:08,467 --> 00:31:10,203
Must you use antibiotics?

378
00:31:11,032 --> 00:31:12,892
Can't you think of other methods?

379
00:31:14,602 --> 00:31:15,772
Besides antibiotics,

380
00:31:15,862 --> 00:31:18,732
I don't believe there's no other
method that can kill the bacteria.

381
00:31:18,822 --> 00:31:20,002
Lower your voice.

382
00:31:22,312 --> 00:31:23,609
Say something.

383
00:31:24,422 --> 00:31:26,004
Aren't you doctors?

384
00:31:26,546 --> 00:31:28,924
I'm sure you have other methods, right?

385
00:31:30,002 --> 00:31:32,325
-Calm down.
-I can't.

386
00:31:33,462 --> 00:31:34,737
Bacteriophage.

387
00:31:36,262 --> 00:31:37,492
What is it?

388
00:31:39,702 --> 00:31:41,587
Bacteriophage is bacteria's worst enemy.

389
00:31:41,667 --> 00:31:43,377
It's a special group of virus...

390
00:31:43,458 --> 00:31:47,556
that parasites on
selectively target bacteria or fungus...

391
00:31:47,636 --> 00:31:49,756
and replicates within bacteria.

392
00:31:49,836 --> 00:31:52,524
It eats and kill bacteria from inside.

393
00:31:53,150 --> 00:31:57,055
It uses physical attack so there
isn't antibiotic resistance problem.

394
00:31:57,135 --> 00:31:58,827
As long as we find
the relevant bacteriophage,

395
00:31:58,907 --> 00:32:01,521
it can kill the Acinetobacter Baumannii
inside his body.

396
00:32:01,601 --> 00:32:02,808
Impossible.

397
00:32:02,888 --> 00:32:04,781
There are many types of bacteriophage.

398
00:32:04,861 --> 00:32:06,814
How do we find it
in such a short period of time?

399
00:32:06,894 --> 00:32:10,273
I've contacted Professor Ye Jun from
Ke Hua University's Biology Lab Center.

400
00:32:10,353 --> 00:32:14,006
His lab
is doing research on phage therapy.

401
00:32:14,086 --> 00:32:16,235
They have collected
many types of bacteriophage.

402
00:32:16,670 --> 00:32:20,180
Moreover, Acinetobacter Baumannii
is on their research list.

403
00:32:20,260 --> 00:32:22,887
He is willing to provide
the phage therapy plan.

404
00:32:22,967 --> 00:32:25,715
Phage therapy?
We have thought about it too.

405
00:32:26,123 --> 00:32:28,881
But it is not part of
mainstream medical practice.

406
00:32:29,316 --> 00:32:32,411
The rise of antibiotics
has completely pushed it aside.

407
00:32:32,491 --> 00:32:35,183
Even if you have this treatment plan,

408
00:32:35,263 --> 00:32:37,783
you won't be able to get approval
from the department in charge.

409
00:32:37,866 --> 00:32:40,355
We may face the risk of breaking the law.

410
00:32:41,085 --> 00:32:42,518
Brigade Commander, Mr Dong Zhi Gang,

411
00:32:42,598 --> 00:32:44,538
has submitted a request
to the higher-ups.

412
00:32:44,618 --> 00:32:47,122
They will try their best
to talk to the department in charge,

413
00:32:47,202 --> 00:32:48,622
and get a special arrangement.

414
00:32:49,058 --> 00:32:52,315
What is the progress of the phage therapy
in their lab?

415
00:32:52,395 --> 00:32:54,050
There is a successful case study.

416
00:32:54,538 --> 00:32:55,652
How many cases?

417
00:32:57,592 --> 00:32:58,664
One.

418
00:33:13,182 --> 00:33:15,282
If the phage therapy has problems,

419
00:33:17,635 --> 00:33:20,818
are we going to lose him forever?

420
00:33:28,702 --> 00:33:30,362
Since he joined the military,

421
00:33:33,102 --> 00:33:35,158
